display="block"><![CDATA[           \operatorname {H}^\bullet (X,G;F)           = \operatorname {H}^\bullet ([X/G]_\bullet ,F^\bullet )         \tag{6.1.2.3}         ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

      (mixed cohomology of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X,G]]></fr:tex> with coefficients in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>).
      Under the hypotheses of (a), if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is the inverse image of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F^{-1}]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S=X/G]]></fr:tex>, then

      <fr:tree
